#tbt Hey there, fit fam! It’s leg day today, and I’m feeling pumped and ready to crush my workout! I know that leg day is often one of the toughest days of the week, but trust me, the results are well worth the effort.

As a bodybuilder, I know just how important it is to work on all areas of the body, and legs are no exception. Your lower body is home to some of the biggest and strongest muscles in your body, and by training them regularly, you can boost your overall strength and fitness levels.

Not only that, but a strong and toned lower body can also help you to achieve that coveted hourglass figure that many women strive for. Plus, working on your legs can help to improve your balance, stability, and overall athletic performance.

So, if you’re feeling tempted to skip leg day today, I urge you to push through that temptation and get to the gym. Whether you’re doing squats, lunges, or deadlifts, make sure you give it your all and challenge yourself to push a little bit harder than you did last time.

Remember, progress is made through consistent effort, so don’t be discouraged if you don’t see immediate results. Keep at it, and you’ll be amazed at just how strong and capable your body can become.

So, let’s do this! Grab your workout gear, head to the gym, and let’s smash leg day together. Trust me, your body will thank you for it later! 💪🏋️‍♀️ #legday #bodybuilding #fitnessmotivation #strongwomen #staystrong #trainhard #dreambig

We have basically 2 kind of movements: 
Compound movements, when we use several muscle groups and joints to execute them ➡️ squats, deadlifts, lunges 
Isolation movements, when we use one specific muscle and joints ➡️ leg extensions, lying and sitting leg curls, adductors, leg press for example 

For a better develop of muscle mass and strength, perform a variety of them in your legs workout.
Start by warming up the muscle group and joints you are going to train, I like leg extensions or sitting leg curls and after I continue with leg press, sitting leg press or adductor BEFORE squats or deadlifts.
I wouldn’t recommend to go straight forward to the bar for squats but is something very common to see 🤷🏽‍♀️

What is the main problem you have when you are starting a “diet plan”?
With more than 20 years of experience giving meal plans, I am going to tell you the main problem is not the time, is not your work, is not your kids, is not money, is not you are tired… your main problem is YOUR MIND! yes, it is immediately making excuses because it is thinking about scarcity and restrictions. 
Hiring a good nutritionist you can find not only strategies to follow your meals according with your activities, tastes, lifestyle in general but help you with your mindset.
These are some tips when you want to cheat on your diet:
1. Keep yourself busy
2. Check if you are doing a lot of cardio, is it really necessary?
3. Before eating a craving take a nap 
4. Before eating a craving drink natural water 
5. Before eating a craving try a cup of coffee
6. Before eating a craving meditate 
Just some tips, there are lots of things we can do to keep on track and #nevergiveup #bodybuilding #nutrition #trainhard #dreambig #staystrong #dowhatyoulove

As women, is not our nature to build muscle and get rid of body fat, actually our hormonal system is highly specialized to work with this fat (under normal conditions), we need it for important biological functions as monthly periods and pregnancy for example. That’s why for us is really hard to remove body fat and that’s not all, even build muscle is not easy, it requieres hours of training everyday by years and a consistent meal plan, many of us use to eat the same everyday by months and then we make those meals more restrictive for some other months.
If you are a regular girl that just want to be healthy and build some muscle foundation, get fun when you train, enjoy looking at your body in a nice shape, don’t be afraid to train with weights by one hour 4 days a week for example and eat healthy in general, that would be enough and you are not going to get a bulky body.

How long do I have to rest between sets?
is a very common question that my clients ask and it makes a lot of sense.

In order to carry out an intense and effective training, within my system I manage the breaks for breaths. Take 5-6 deep breaths, inhale through the nose, hold the air inside the thorax for 4-5 seconds and then slowly exhale through the mouth.

While you are breathing, you can be moving to accommodate the equipment you need to do the next series or just stay breathing.

This type of breathing will allow you to recover faster and generate more energy for the next series, very long rests ruin your efforts to maintain blood flow to the muscle you are working, the intensity of the training is lost and therefore the stimulus is not enough to oxidize fat or to create muscle growth.
